description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domestic Operative (Cleaner)– bank opportunities with NBTeXtra, Competitive pay rates.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So, you’re eager to learn more about working as a bank Domestic Operative (Cleaner) in North Bristol NHS Trust. Here’s some of the reasons we’re unique…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are a centre of excellence for health care in the South West in a number of fields as well as being one of the largest hospital trusts in the UK- NBT is a Major Trauma centre and regional specialist for Neurosciences, Renal, Burns and Plastics, Orthopaedics and Urology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our values mean we are passionate about great care at North Bristol Trust and our patients know our primary focus is to provide ‘Exceptional Healthcare, Personally Delivered’&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State of the art facilities- you will be based within our award winning Brunel building, which has recently won Best Acute Hospital Development at the 2017 Building Better Healthcare Awards in London and Best Healthcare Design over 25,000sqm at the European Healthcare Awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;But it’s not just our Trust which is exciting; our Trust bank NBTeXtra is innovative, impressive and inclusive. Let us tell you a little more about it…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NBTeXtra bank workers are valued members of our team and have access to exceptional benefits, including access to the NHS Pension scheme, free DBS and full training and induction support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will increase your skill set by working with multidisciplinary teams to deliver all aspects of patient care and may have the opportunity to establish regular work across some units&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NBTeXtra offer flexible working patterns to meet your needs, offering earlies, lates, long days and nights with competitive rates.
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In a Domestic Operative role, you will be paid at band 2:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£10.03* per hour- Week days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£13.96* per hour- Nights and Saturdays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;£17.89* per hour- Sundays and Bank Holidays&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*All rates are inclusive of annual leave allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Right, that’s enough about us… let’s focus on you. Are you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excited at the prospect of delivering an essential service, delivering general ward, theatre and departmental cleaning, including infection deep cleans as required?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about ensuring the delivery of high standards of cleanliness required in a hospital environment?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible to support the needs of the Trust and our patients?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, Apply Now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vicky Packer: Vicky.Packer@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
